{"type":182,"children":183,"toc":443},"root",[184,193,200,206,212,217,258,272,278,283,294,300,305,311,316,327,333,338,344,349,357,379,384,390,395,404,415,420],{"type":185,"tag":186,"props":187,"children":189},"element","h2",{"id":188},"quick-questions",[190],{"type":191,"value":192},"text","Quick Questions",{"type":185,"tag":194,"props":195,"children":197},"h4",{"id":196},"gitflow-是什么",[198],{"type":191,"value":199},"Gitflow 是什么？",{"type":185,"tag":201,"props":202,"children":203},"p",{},[204],{"type":191,"value":205},"Gitflow 是一种使用 Git 合作时使用的工作流程。与之类似的概念有 Centralized Workflow、Feature Branch Workflow、Forking Workflow 等。",{"type":185,"tag":194,"props":207,"children":209},{"id":208},"选用工作流前需要注意什么",[210],{"type":191,"value":211},"选用工作流前需要注意什么？",{"type":185,"tag":201,"props":213,"children":214},{},[215],{"type":191,"value":216},"工作流应该是“指南”，而不是手册，没有一种工作流程是能解决所有问题而没有显著副作用的，所以应该根据团队规模、业务流程（如需求大小、需求频次）选用更适合团队的工作流。",{"type":185,"tag":218,"props":219,"children":220},"ul",{},[221,235,247],{"type":185,"tag":222,"props":223,"children":224},"li",{},[225,227,233],{"type":191,"value":226},"工作流能否",{"type":185,"tag":228,"props":229,"children":230},"strong",{},[231],{"type":191,"value":232},"容错",{"type":191,"value":234},"，或是可以避免犯错？",{"type":185,"tag":222,"props":236,"children":237},{},[238,240,245],{"type":191,"value":239},"工作流能否可以随着团队人数变更而",{"type":185,"tag":228,"props":241,"children":242},{},[243],{"type":191,"value":244},"扩展",{"type":191,"value":246},"？",{"type":185,"tag":222,"props":248,"children":249},{},[250,252,257],{"type":191,"value":251},"工作流能否带来了不必要的",{"type":185,"tag":228,"props":253,"children":254},{},[255],{"type":191,"value":256},"认知负担",{"type":191,"value":246},{"type":185,"tag":201,"props":259,"children":260},{},[261,263],{"type":191,"value":262},"见：",{"type":185,"tag":264,"props":265,"children":269},"a",{"href":266,"rel":267},"http://fresky.github.io/2020/03/10/common-branching-models/",[268],"nofollow",[270],{"type":191,"value":271},"常见的代码分支模型和比较",{"type":185,"tag":194,"props":273,"children":275},{"id":274},"centralized-workflow-是怎么运作的",[276],{"type":191,"value":277},"Centralized Workflow 是怎么运作的？",{"type":185,"tag":201,"props":279,"children":280},{},[281],{"type":191,"value":282},"如果其他版本管理工具过渡到 Git，那么 Centralized Workflow 是学习成本最小的方案。在此工作流中，团队成员围绕 main 分支开发：拉取代码、开发，然后提交，就这么简单。因为没有额外的分支，所以 main 分支的历史记录开起来像是一条干净的线，这种感觉就像是传统的 SVN 工作流一样。",{"type":185,"tag":201,"props":284,"children":285},{},[286,287],{"type":191,"value":262},{"type":185,"tag":264,"props":288,"children":291},{"href":289,"rel":290},"https://trunkbaseddevelopment.com/",[268],[292],{"type":191,"value":293},"Trunk Based Development",{"type":185,"tag":194,"props":295,"children":297},{"id":296},"feature-branch-workflow-是怎么运作的",[298],{"type":191,"value":299},"Feature Branch Workflow 是怎么运作的？",{"type":185,"tag":201,"props":301,"children":302},{},[303],{"type":191,"value":304},"Feature Branch Workflow 是在 Centraolized Workflow 之上的扩展。开发人员在单独的 feature 分支开发新功能，然后通过 PR 请求提交回 main 分支。在需要帮助时，可以提前请求 PR，邀请他们代码审阅或是提交修复。这种流程隐含的约定是：main 分支上的代码一定是可用的（至少测试通过，能跑），这种小步快跑的模式对持续集成环境来说是一个巨大的优势。",{"type":185,"tag":194,"props":306,"children":308},{"id":307},"pr-是什么",[309],{"type":191,"value":310},"PR 是什么？",{"type":185,"tag":201,"props":312,"children":313},{},[314],{"type":191,"value":315},"Pull Request（PR）是一种使用 GitLab 或其它版本管理系统附带的一种工作流程。PR 可以作为一种告知团队其它成员当前分支功能已经完成的提醒。每个 PR 还附带有代码变更内容和讨论区，团队成员可以通过 PR 进行 Code Review，讨论方案，或者评论代码。使开发人员从邮件或者即时通讯软件中解脱出来。",{"type":185,"tag":201,"props":317,"children":318},{},[319,320],{"type":191,"value":262},{"type":185,"tag":264,"props":321,"children":324},{"href":322,"rel":323},"https://guides.github.com/introduction/flow/",[268],[325],{"type":191,"value":326},"GitHub flow",{"type":185,"tag":194,"props":328,"children":330},{"id":329},"forking-workflow-是怎么运作的",[331],{"type":191,"value":332},"Forking Workflow 是怎么运作的？",{"type":185,"tag":201,"props":334,"children":335},{},[336],{"type":191,"value":337},"在 Forking Workflow 流程中，开发使用单独的仓库来开发一个完整的功能，一旦功能开发完毕，再通过 PR 合并回主仓库 main 分支。因为主仓库管理员并不关心代码的具体实现，所以开发没有主仓库的写入权限，Code Review 也不用在主仓库进行。",{"type":185,"tag":194,"props":339,"children":341},{"id":340},"gitflow-workflow-是怎么运作的",[342],{"type":191,"value":343},"Gitflow Workflow 是怎么运作的？",{"type":185,"tag":201,"props":345,"children":346},{},[347],{"type":191,"value":348},"Gitflow Workflow 最早在 Vincent Driessen 2010 年写的一篇博客中被提出。作为 Feature Branch Workflow 的补充，它仅仅是规范各分支的行为。不同分支有不同的作用，比方说 release 分支用来测试，main 分支用来发布，hotfix 分支用来提交热修复，等等。Gitflow 还规定了分支与分支应该如何合并。",{"type":185,"tag":201,"props":350,"children":351},{},[352],{"type":185,"tag":353,"props":354,"children":356},"img",{"alt":179,"src":355},"https://mgear-image.oss-cn-shanghai.aliyuncs.com/image/other/20220627173845.png?w=40",[],{"type":185,"tag":201,"props":358,"children":359},{},[360,361,368,370,377],{"type":191,"value":262},{"type":185,"tag":264,"props":362,"children":365},{"href":363,"rel":364},"https://www.atlassian.com/git/tutorials/comparing-workflows/gitflow-workflow",[268],[366],{"type":191,"value":367},"Gitflow Workflow",{"type":191,"value":369},"、",{"type":185,"tag":264,"props":371,"children":374},{"href":372,"rel":373},"https://nvie.com/posts/a-successful-git-branching-model/",[268],[375],{"type":191,"value":376},"A successful Git branching model",{"type":191,"value":378},"，在 2020 年的补充中，作者提及类似 Web 应用这种不需要经常回滚的应用，使用更简单的 GitHub Flow 可能会更合适。",{"type":185,"tag":186,"props":380,"children":382},{"id":381},"评价",[383],{"type":191,"value":381},{"type":185,"tag":194,"props":385,"children":387},{"id":386},"gitflow-的负面影响",[388],{"type":191,"value":389},"Gitflow 的负面影响？",{"type":185,"tag":201,"props":391,"children":392},{},[393],{"type":191,"value":394},"Thoughtworks 认为短生命周期的分支策略给实施 CI/CD 带来更小的伤害，反之类似 Gitflow 中经常用到的长生命周期分治策略反而是在鼓励后期集成（late integration）。",{"type":185,"tag":201,"props":396,"children":397},{},[398],{"type":185,"tag":399,"props":400,"children":401},"q",{},[402],{"type":191,"value":403},"We firmly believe that long-lived version-control branches harm valuable engineering practieces such as CI, and this belief underlies our dislike for Gitflow.",{"type":185,"tag":201,"props":405,"children":406},{},[407,408],{"type":191,"value":262},{"type":185,"tag":264,"props":409,"children":412},{"href":410,"rel":411},"https://www.thoughtworks.com/cn/radar/techniques/long-lived-branches-with-gitflow",[268],[413],{"type":191,"value":414},"Gitflow long-lived-branch on Tech Radar",{"type":185,"tag":186,"props":416,"children":418},{"id":417},"相关资源",[419],{"type":191,"value":417},{"type":185,"tag":218,"props":421,"children":422},{},[423,433],{"type":185,"tag":222,"props":424,"children":425},{},[426],{"type":185,"tag":264,"props":427,"children":430},{"href":428,"rel":429},"https://devblogs.microsoft.com/oldnewthing/20180323-01/?p=98325",[268],[431],{"type":191,"value":432},"Stop cherry-picking, start merging",{"type":185,"tag":222,"props":434,"children":435},{},[436],{"type":185,"tag":264,"props":437,"children":440},{"href":438,"rel":439},"https://martinfowler.com/articles/branching-patterns.html",[268],[441],{"type":191,"value":442},"Patterns for Managing Source Code Branches",{"title":178,"searchDepth":444,"depth":444,"links":445},2,[446,447,448],{"id":188,"depth":444,"text":192},{"id":381,"depth":444,"text":381},{"id":417,"depth":444,"text":417},"markdown","content:6.maps:_devops:git:gitflow.md","content","6.maps/_devops/git/gitflow.md","6.maps/_devops/git/gitflow","md",[456,460],{"_path":457,"title":458,"description":459},"/maps/_devops/git/dorothy","Dorothy","Dorothy 是我的 Git Commit Message 的约定。",{"_path":461,"title":462,"description":463},"/maps/_devops/git/pre-commit-hook","Pre Commit Hook","title: 预提交钩子（Pre-commit hooks）\ndescription: Git 的 pre-commit hook 用来在提交代码前执行一些检查或操作",1771696725133]